-- European Stocks Decline for a Third Day as North Korea Shells South Korea
-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 2010-11-23T08:03:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/european-stocks-decline-for-a-third-day-as-north-korea-shells-south-korea.html
European stocks dropped for a third
day, extending a global selloff, after North Korea fired
artillery shells into South Korea. U.S. stock-index futures and
Asian equities also retreated.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index slid 0.5 percent to 266.31 at
8:03 a.m. in London.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  